e2e2099a94bd35e6ec571b5a6b5dd.png\" width=\"560\" alt=\"Windows 8 Start Menu\"></noscript></p>\n<p>Heat map of time to reach tiles in the Start screen from the Start button<br>\n(green tiles are the fastest to get to, red tiles are the slowest)</p>\n<p>That's not to say it doesn't have its problems, I like to use the Windows 8.1 mail application. I like it because I can pin it to my start screen and get notifications on the tile for any new emails. As a heavy desktop user though, I want to open the application on the desktop in a window and not in the full screen touch friendly window. Happily though :), this is going to be fixed in the next update where <a href=\"http://www.wpcentral.com/more-windows-81-update-leaks-appear-apps-desktop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">WinRT apps can now be run on the good old desktop</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 682 512' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-0abc8d52e3a0364ca02be154d55374e2'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-0abc8d52e3a0364ca02be154d55374e2)' width='682' height='512' xlink:href='data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2bvTBlDUUEs7rDk0N3YqIzWSdb7WJ/LFhcU1MeSwnh5csoUaZY5peWdTxMbkK2/hbe5XsR0xAsgioRKzV8scA1PplZWJU3NjYHext1xn9S1rSk4U4ZXKgxVUaNgkkcdSeYSRuBc9e2KdyqegoaUx1clORHI/hkN2HiPl36Ys/MeIUXLjTSToJGhUNKadgNbIGB1Dz8X7X6YiOQ8L5pnDyJTZXS1pudeizHr31DE%2bPFd7jJPyB4apJeKuI6OhyUxBoy0rMx0hU7%2bu9hbDpUNQ2WZVQUsySyyR06KzRREgkAA27e2Fgymmf4c5skvEWRxUlPVLuUUM%2bkE%2bQYnTbrhpcrqxLw/R1GXsY4ZI0aMIDbQUuNrH0xp49ijZ5ogllp8yjkXVIsse9tLxMD%2b18cesQ1Kus0ixBSDHyW3Pe9r4KieulQMrkA3uCQPbquCqXnhWE5JN9jqB2/IDGvtRqQeeslbn1HN11LOXaRjcsxN774Ci%2b204RgNbjUQO5N8BvVfZWjDIHdgPFta%2bCaWirYq5LmnjQ6VVjUJ1vbpe9sTjVNrQPQVfy5tNJSwOY8nkRtUam0yRmIOf7thv1wqtJUzZfBDLExWoh8QJ/71xPst4pr6T4dZrw0zwBqqpR4h9ISwjO8vn3Vf8ALFdR0VdVSyyXpvGrDT9IQEWNu%2bGfIjBVCriM9ZMzysNJdyf09vbDqcJGpXhDKRR8vUIYA2s/h0C9vXCGZZXq1PJDL0N/1w9vBqxS8F5SJ5GReTARbz8A2wHGl6UhU1wkJZdaXO2w28t7YJJmH4Ivzc/6x5yw0UjyMWdW1EEuLXPcbb4z0sVNBIeRNpLMAQLbnt0wp2tRqmYSKZLMAwJtvexxIpc7pxJHPHRQo4AK/Uxkat9z6b9PQY7qsggoQnMrKSaWKjSvkeCrSRCG6Itvx36r5WxIa/g%2bWqrstSatoC1dTiaIpUBUiULfS/krddu%2bFkmHWXuaV/KODiCRYhH9GoX2%2b80Ck7evvgGauNXVtO8UMZ0aTy1Cg%2btsSir4Uqa3LaSYz0qpI4jj1OFKk7AufJem/TriJZo8uUzVGU1LwyiJtPMp7MrG97hj1GAyHkzLHLl50etQ8kZ331L3xsQ%2bGapPwRlPNQN9mgNj5HlrjXVDNEBIJeYLo2nRb73le/lhquA/mCyXL%2bGFpRldSWy%2blj5plqoIi%2blQv1as13O3Qb4o4yy6TJrTQre0SG5uSVBx9CCFSCsUYINwQo2wvn80eQ6S38CzAgDV/Xhv7W1dcZB8zmSmCWUcP5nojNjaWI39rNvhajd//9k=' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"682\" alt=\"Windows 8 app running on Desktop\" data-srcset=\"/assets/static/Windows-8-app-on-Desktop.8827e8a.7793c73c790cac622f4523bac66c71d5.jpg 682w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 682px) 100vw, 682px\" data-src=\"/assets/static/Windows-8-app-on-Desktop.8827e8a.7793c73c790cac622f4523bac66c71d5.jpg\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/assets/static/Windows-8-app-on-Desktop.8827e8a.7793c73c790cac622f4523bac66c71d5.jpg\" width=\"682\" alt=\"Windows 8 app running on Desktop\"></noscript></p>\n<p>Windows 8 Bing Finance app running on Desktop</p>\n<p>Ihave been looking to replace my trusty old non-touch screen Samsung laptop running Windows 8.1 with a new touch screen model. However, I like to shoot a few HE shells at some tanks while playing <a href=\"http://worldoftanks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">World of Tanks</a> on the weekend in my down time. Its not the most demanding of games but I'd like to look forward to future updates and other games like Battlefield 4.</p>\n<p>So I've been doing my research on what my options are for a touch screen gaming laptop and was very surprised to discover that they are pretty non-existent. The closest thing you'll find is the <a href=\"http://www.notebookcheck.net/Review-Asus-N550JV-CN201H-Notebook.98311.0.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Asus N550JV-CN201H</a>, which is not really a gaming laptop with an <a href=\"http://www.notebookcheck.net/NVIDIA-GeForce-GT-750M.90245.0.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">nVidia GT750M</a> low to mid-range graphics card. It'll play today's games at mid-range settings and will probably choke on tomorrows games altogether.</p>\n<p>Why is this? Well after some reading I get the impression that laptop manufacturers believe that enthusiasts don't like glossy screens and adding a touch screen means adding a glossy layer on top of the screen. This I think is personal preference, I have seen one matt screened touch screen laptop in the wild but I can't remember where, so it is at least possible to have a matt screen. So why the delay?</p>\n<p>What I really want is the <a href=\"http://www.notebookcheck.net/Review-MSI-GS70-65M21621-Notebook.102287.0.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">MSI GS70 Stealth</a> but with a touch screen. This is the worlds thinnest 17\" laptop with an Intel i7 CPU, a GT765M mid to high end graphics card and even a SSD RAID 0 array. Overall its a very impressive beast packed into a small a space as possible.</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 600 480' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-24bde47fc9980ed635fc636efc1a95e2'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-24bde47fc9980ed635fc636efc1a95e2)' width='600' height='480' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAzCAYAAAAn3w6xAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAXIElEQVRo3u1beZRcdZWu6j3dtdert6%2b1dnV19ZbuLJ09IQkkDQkhQAyRIWGRRWQXQlhCAgECBmQLguwgoywiYBRQHMDARBbFCQ4CxzlnNDo